casebody.data:
Alexander, Appellant, v. Carey, Appellee.

[Cite as Alexander v. Carey (1992), 62 Ohio St.3d 409.]

*410(No. 91-587 Submitted September 17, 1991 Decided January 29, 1992.) James I. Alexander, pro se. Per Curiam.

The court of appeals did not have jurisdiction. Section 3, Article IV, Ohio Constitution. Consequently, we affirm the judgment of the court of appeals.

Judgment affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
